<subsection xml:id="subsec-Code-food">
  <title>Code</title>
  <term>Source code </term>
  <program>
    #include &lt;dht.h&gt;//header files
      dht DHT;//define function 
      int t=0;//initialize t.
      int h=0;// initialize h
      #define //DHT11_PIN 8 define pin D8
      #define //MQ3_PIN A0 define A0
      char data = 0;
      int gas_read = 0; //define gas sensor
      void setup() 
      {                
      Serial.begin(9600); // enable software serial
      pinMode(MQ3_PIN, INPUT);//mode declaration
      }
      void loop()// the loop
      {
      gas_read = analogRead(MQ3_PIN);//convert value of gas sensor as analog value
      Serial.print(gas_read);//print value of gas sensor 
      int chk = DHT.read11(DHT11_PIN);//read the Temperature and humidity
      Serial.print("Temperature = ");// print value of temperature 
      t = DHT.temperature;
      Serial.println(t);
      Serial.print("Humidity = "); print value of humidity 
      int h = DHT.humidity;
      Serial.println(h);
      }      
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation </term>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Declaring pins of Gas sensor and DHT11.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Defining the dht pin as 8 and MQ3 pin as A0. At the beginning of the program variable gas read is initialized to zero. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Function dht DHT () is initialized.   
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void setup() declaring MQ3 and DHT pin as input pin using Pinmode function. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void loop function, converting the data generated from MQ3 sensor to analog data using analogRead function and converting the data generated from DHT11 sensor to read data variable using DHT11. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The parameter humidity, temperature is saved in and instance variable called h and t. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        As this is a monitoring system there is no output modules are used.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
